President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. James O'Brien will be the Special Presidential Envoy for Hostage Affairs at the Department of State. Charles "Chip" Lyons will be the United States Representative on the Executive Board of the United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF), while Aaron Williams will be the United States Alternate Representative on the same board. Esther Brimmer and Michael Guest will be appointed as members of the National Security Education Board. These individuals bring a wealth of experience and dedication to their roles, and President Obama looks forward to working with them.